HEADWORD: Boorish
<hw>Boor"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like a boor; clownish; uncultured;
unmannerly.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Boor"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Boor"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which is in truth a gross and <qex>boorish</qex> opinion.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boort</ent>⟦br⟧
